                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13005932" author="jnp" created="Sat, 12 Mar 2011 00:37:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed change:&lt;br/&gt;
   FileContext object should remember the user (UGI) for which it was created, and any AbstractFileSystem object should be created for that user i.e. within a doAs for that user.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13005933" author="jnp" created="Sat, 12 Mar 2011 00:41:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch uploaded.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019979" author="jnp" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 18:48:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch against latest trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020067" author="jnp" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 22:24:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Previous patch missed a place where AbstractFileSystem was created.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020368" author="sureshms" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2011 17:35:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Comments:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While creating RunTimeException, do you want to wrap the exception you caught to provide more details in RunTimeException.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a good idea to document in public APIs that RunTimeException may be thrown and the reason for that exception.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When logging the exception, you are doing LOG.warn(msg + ex) instead of LOG.warn(msg, ex). Is this intentional?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13020437" author="jnp" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2011 21:21:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch addressing the comments.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020438" author="sureshms" created="Fri, 15 Apr 2011 21:23:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
